l was just buying a part for the Rabbit.

64
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:52,488
You should really come
take a ride when it's done.

65
00:06:52,588 --> 00:06:53,990
Is it fast?

66
00:06:54,090 --> 00:06:55,783
Um.

67
00:06:55,883 --> 00:06:57,883
It’s decent.

68
00:06:58,135 --> 00:07:00,430
I’m kidding.
- Okay. Good.

69
00:07:01,138 --> 00:07:03,264
Hey, happy birthday.

70
00:07:04,809 --> 00:07:07,104
Your dad told my dad, so...

71
00:07:07,645 --> 00:07:09,645
Yeah, of course he did.

72
00:07:10,147 --> 00:07:13,887
I saw this the other day and thought of you.

73
00:07:14,318 --> 00:07:16,318
Catches bad dreams.

74
00:07:18,155 --> 00:07:20,156
That's kind of perfect.

75
00:07:22,326 --> 00:07:24,186
Thank you.

76
00:07:24,286 --> 00:07:26,286
No problem.

77
00:07:27,998 --> 00:07:29,066
Good seeing you.
- Yeah, I’ll see you later.

78
00:07:29,166 --> 00:07:31,166
Bye.

79
00:07:31,752 --> 00:07:36,532
So how come Jacob Black
gets to give you a gift and I don't?

80
00:07:36,632 --> 00:07:40,077
Because I have nothing to give back to you.

81
00:07:40,177 --> 00:07:44,172
Bella, you give me everything
just by breathing.

82
00:07:45,015 --> 00:07:47,015
See? Thank you.

83
00:07:47,143 --> 00:07:49,353
That's all l want.
- Bella.

84
00:07:50,771 --> 00:07:52,981
Happy birthday.
- Shh, shh.

85
00:07:55,776 --> 00:07:56,927
I thought I said no presents.

86
00:07:57,027 --> 00:07:59,138
I've already seen you
open it, and guess what,

87
00:07:59,238 --> 00:08:00,639
you love it.

88
00:08:00,739 --> 00:08:04,139
You're gonna wear it tonight. Our place.

89
00:08:05,286 --> 00:08:08,288
Come on. Please? It'll be fun.

90
00:08:11,917 --> 00:08:14,294
Okay. All right.
- Great.

91
00:08:14,378 --> 00:08:16,843
Okay, I’ll see you at 7:00.

92
00:08:18,549 --> 00:08:22,289
Jasper, no fair with the mood control thing.

93
00:08:23,095 --> 00:08:25,680
Sorry, Bella. Happy...

94
00:08:27,016 --> 00:08:29,016
Never mind.

95
00:08:30,686 --> 00:08:33,938
You can't trust vampires. Trust me.

96
00:08:34,899 --> 00:08:36,983
O my love. My wife.

97
00:08:37,776 --> 00:08:39,929
Death, that hath sucked
the honey of thy breath...

98
00:08:40,029 --> 00:08:43,514
...hath had no power yet upon thy beauty.

99
00:08:43,616 --> 00:08:45,616
Thou art not conquered.

100
00:08:46,952 --> 00:08:51,607
Beauty's ensign yet is crimson
in thy lips and in thy cheeks.

101
00:08:51,707 --> 00:08:54,527
And death's pale flag is not advanced there.

102
00:08:54,627 --> 00:08:56,667
I hate being celebrated.

103
00:08:57,296 --> 00:09:00,199
There are worse tragedies.
l mean, look at Romeo.

104
00:09:00,299 --> 00:09:04,039
Killed his true love out of sheer stupidity.

105
00:09:05,179 --> 00:09:06,664
Yeah.

106
00:09:06,764 --> 00:09:09,399
Though l do envy him one thing.

107
00:09:10,809 --> 00:09:12,934
Juliet is, like, perfect.

108
00:09:12,937 --> 00:09:17,187
If you like that obviously
beautiful sort of thing.

109
00:09:19,485 --> 00:09:22,445
Not the girl, the suicide.

110
00:09:26,367 --> 00:09:29,002
It’s nearly impossible for...

111
00:09:30,079 --> 00:09:32,705
For some people.

112
00:09:35,376 --> 00:09:38,628
For humans, a little poison,

113
00:09:40,714 --> 00:09:42,715
a dagger to the heart.

114
00:09:44,009 --> 00:09:46,899
There's so many different options.

115
00:09:49,848 --> 00:09:51,848
Why would you say that?

116
00:09:53,060 --> 00:09:55,950
Because I had to consider it once.

117
00:09:57,773 --> 00:10:00,342
I didn't know if I’d get to you in time.

118
00:10:00,442 --> 00:10:03,842
I had to come up with some kind of plan.

119
00:10:04,863 --> 00:10:06,557
What was the plan?

120
00:10:06,657 --> 00:10:10,652
That I’d go to Italy and provoke the Volturi.

121
00:10:10,953 --> 00:10:13,162
The what?
- The Volturi.

122
00:10:13,247 --> 00:10:16,692
Now, who'd like to repeat
the last few lines of iambic pentameter...

123
00:10:16,792 --> 00:10:19,653
...just to show they were paying attention?

124
00:10:19,753 --> 00:10:21,753
Mr Cullen?

125
00:10:24,174 --> 00:10:26,174
Yes, Mr Berty.

126
00:10:28,554 --> 00:10:32,432
'O here will I set up my everlasting rest...

127
00:10:34,435 --> 00:10:39,340
'and shake the yoke of inauspicious stars
from this world-wearied flesh.

128
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:41,440
'Eyes, look your last.

129
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:44,450
'Arms, take your last embrace.

130
00:10:45,154 --> 00:10:48,469
'And, lips, O you, the doors of breath,

131
00:10:48,699 --> 00:10:54,394
'seal with a righteous kiss a dateless
bargain to engrossing death.'

132
00:10:55,289 --> 00:10:57,584
Eyes on the screen, people.

133
00:10:59,043 --> 00:11:01,377
Thus with a kiss I die.

134
00:11:04,715 --> 00:11:08,452
The Volturi are a very old,
very powerful family.

135
00:11:08,552 --> 00:11:12,706
l guess they're the closest thing
to royalty my world has.

136
00:11:12,806 --> 00:11:15,016
Is that Carlisle?
- Yeah.

137
00:11:16,226 --> 00:11:18,379
He lived with them for a few decades.

138
00:11:18,479 --> 00:11:23,926
Described them as very refined.
No respect for human life, of course,

139
00:11:24,026 --> 00:11:28,531
but a respect for the arts
and the sciences, at least.

140
00:11:29,031 --> 00:11:31,031
And the law.

141
00:11:31,533 --> 00:11:33,533
Above all, the law.

142
00:11:36,538 --> 00:11:38,538
Vampires have laws?

143
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:41,833
Not very many.

144
00:11:42,628 --> 00:11:45,943
And only one that's regularly enforced.

145
00:11:47,966 --> 00:11:49,966
What is it?

146
00:11:50,511 --> 00:11:53,956
That we keep the existence
of our kind a secret.

147
00:11:54,056 --> 00:11:57,286
We don't make spectacles of ourselves,

148
00:11:58,977 --> 00:12:01,697
and we don't kill conspicuously.

149
00:12:05,442 --> 00:12:08,417
Unless, of course, you want to die.

150
00:12:22,376 --> 00:12:24,361
You gotta stop talking about that.

151
00:12:24,461 --> 00:12:28,256
I can't even think about
someone hurting you.

152
00:12:30,843 --> 00:12:34,929
Bella, the only thing
that can hurt me is you.

153
00:12:37,307 --> 00:12:39,752
And I don't have anything
else to be afraid of.

154
00:12:39,852 --> 00:12:41,852
That's not true.

155
00:12:43,397 --> 00:12:46,542
Victoria? She'll come for me one day.

156
00:12:47,067 --> 00:12:51,571
Alice will see when she
decides, and we'll be ready.

157
00:12:51,822 --> 00:12:53,822
I could protect you...

158
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:56,700
...if you change me.

159
00:12:57,161 --> 00:12:59,966
Bella, you already do protect me.

160
00:13:01,540 --> 00:13:03,580
You're my only reason...

161
00:13:05,169 --> 00:13:07,169
...to stay alive,

162
00:13:07,629 --> 00:13:09,629
if that's what I am.

163
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:14,435
But it's my job to protect you.

164
00:13:17,681 --> 00:13:20,767
From everyone except my sister.

165
00:13:20,851 --> 00:13:25,186
It’s time. It’s time. It’s time. It’s time.

166
00:13:34,865 --> 00:13:36,517
Sorry about all this.

167
00:13:36,617 --> 00:13:39,436
We tried to rein Alice in.
- As if that were even possible.

168
00:13:39,536 --> 00:13:42,171
Happy birthday, Bella.
- Thanks.

169
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,960
I found it in your bag. You mind?

170
00:13:48,712 --> 00:13:51,007
Dating an older woman. Hot.

171
00:13:53,175 --> 00:13:55,385
What?
- You first, Rosalie.

172
00:13:58,263 --> 00:14:01,578
It’s a necklace. Alice picked it out.

173
00:14:01,767 --> 00:14:03,767
Thanks.

174
00:14:05,729 --> 00:14:07,729
Show me the love.

175
00:14:11,109 --> 00:14:13,110
This one's from Emmett.

176
00:14:15,572 --> 00:14:18,058
Already installed it in your truck.

177
00:14:18,158 --> 00:14:19,560
Finally a decent sound system...

178
00:14:19,660 --> 00:14:23,147
...for that piece of...
- Hey. Don't hate the truck.

179
00:14:23,247 --> 00:14:25,414
Open Esme and Carlisle's.

180
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:29,153
Just a little something to brighten your day.

181
00:14:29,253 --> 00:14:33,078
Yes, you've been looking kind of pale lately.

182
00:14:37,511 --> 00:14:39,511
Ow.

183
00:14:40,264 --> 00:14:42,264
Paper cut.

184
00:15:06,331 --> 00:15:10,241
Jaz, Jaz. It’s okay. It’s just a little...

185
00:15:11,795 --> 00:15:13,795
...blood.

186
00:15:19,636 --> 00:15:21,636
Get Jasper out of here.

187
00:15:27,311 --> 00:15:29,604
I’m sorry, I can't.

188
00:15:31,899 --> 00:15:35,554
I’ll have to stitch this up in my office.

189
00:15:36,987 --> 00:15:38,987
Check on Jasper.

190
00:15:39,406 --> 00:15:40,849
I’m sure he's very upset with himself,

191
00:15:40,949 --> 00:15:44,394
and I doubt he'll listen to anyone
but you right now.

192
00:15:44,494 --> 00:15:46,494
Edward.

193
00:15:57,174 --> 00:16:01,849
l never wanted to have a party.
- It’s not your fault.

194
00:16:02,721 --> 00:16:07,501
Jasper hasn't been away from human
blood as long as the rest of us.

195
00:16:07,601 --> 00:16:09,601
How do you do it?

196
00:16:10,187 --> 00:16:12,567
Years and years of practice.

197
00:16:12,856 --> 00:16:16,936
Did you ever think of just
doing it the easy way?

198
00:16:18,570 --> 00:16:20,570
No.

199
00:16:20,822 --> 00:16:25,072
I knew who I wanted to be.
I wanted to help people.

200
00:16:25,452 --> 00:16:30,042
It brings me happiness, even
if l am damned regardless.

201
00:16:31,249 --> 00:16:33,249
Damned?

202
00:16:33,543 --> 00:16:36,295
Like hell?

203
00:16:42,719 --> 00:16:45,524
Carlisle, you couldn't be damned.

204
00:16:45,555 --> 00:16:48,275
You couldn't. It’s impossible.

205
00:16:48,350 --> 00:16:49,960
Thank you, Bella.

206
00:16:50,060 --> 00:16:54,188
You've always been very gracious about us.

207
00:16:58,235 --> 00:17:01,890
So that's it?
That's why he won't change me?

208
00:17:04,574 --> 00:17:07,804
Imagine the situation in reverse. Hmm.

209
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:11,714
If you believed as Edward does,

210
00:17:12,874 --> 00:17:15,339
could you take away his soul?

211
00:17:38,275 --> 00:17:40,275
You can't protect me...

212
00:17:42,279 --> 00:17:44,279
...from everything.

213
00:17:44,406 --> 00:17:48,146
At some point, something's
gonna separate us.

214
00:17:49,077 --> 00:17:52,562
It’s gonna be an accident or illness...

215
00:17:52,873 --> 00:17:54,873
...or old age,

216
00:17:56,043 --> 00:18:01,228
as long as I’m human.
And the only solution is to change me.

217
00:18:02,924 --> 00:18:05,619
That's not a solution. That's a tragedy.

218
00:18:05,719 --> 00:18:10,394
You're not gonna want me when
I look like a grandmother.

219
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:23,115
Bella, do you not understand
my feelings for you at all?

220
00:18:25,614 --> 00:18:27,614
Carlisle told me...

221
00:18:30,494 --> 00:18:33,214
...how you feel about your soul.

222
00:18:34,206 --> 00:18:36,206
I don't believe that.

223
00:18:37,209 --> 00:18:39,419
So don't worry about mine.

224
00:18:40,462 --> 00:18:42,462
You should go inside.

225
00:18:57,020 --> 00:18:59,145
It’s still my birthday.

226
00:19:02,567 --> 00:19:04,568
So can I ask one thing?

227
00:19:08,156 --> 00:19:10,156
Kiss me?

228
00:19:40,814 --> 00:19:46,193
I love you.

229
00:20:15,098 --> 00:20:17,308
Up with your turret

230
00:20:19,603 --> 00:20:23,564
Aren't we just terrified?

231
00:20:35,243 --> 00:20:38,746
Shale, screen your worry

232
00:20:39,789 --> 00:20:43,792
From what you won't ever find

233
00:20:53,178 --> 00:21:01,477
Don't let it fool you

234
00:21:02,145 --> 00:21:04,188
Down

235
00:21:08,109 --> 00:21:10,109
Hey.

236
00:21:13,198 --> 00:21:15,748
Just come take a walk with me.

237
00:21:39,432 --> 00:21:41,432
We have to leave Forks.

238
00:21:44,646 --> 00:21:46,646
Why?

239
00:21:49,484 --> 00:21:52,929
Carlisle's supposed to be 10
years older than he looks,

240
00:21:53,029 --> 00:21:55,919
and people are starting to notice.

241
00:21:58,118 --> 00:22:02,793
Okay, I’ve gotta think of
something to say to Charlie.

242
00:22:13,967 --> 00:22:15,967
When you say 'we'...

243
00:22:20,056 --> 00:22:22,436
I mean my family and myself.

244
00:22:26,438 --> 00:22:30,258
Edward, what happened with
Jasper, it's nothing.

245
00:22:30,358 --> 00:22:33,068
You're right. It was nothing,

246
00:22:35,655 --> 00:22:38,800
nothing but what l always expected...

247
00:22:40,201 --> 00:22:44,536
...and nothing compared to
what could have happened.

248
00:22:49,419 --> 00:22:52,904
You just don't belong in my world, Bella.

249
00:22:57,302 --> 00:22:59,302
I belong with you.

250
00:23:00,764 --> 00:23:03,098
No. You don't.

251
00:23:05,602 --> 00:23:07,602
I’m coming.

252
00:23:08,104 --> 00:23:10,104
Bella,

253
00:23:10,690 --> 00:23:13,025
I don't want you to come.

254
00:23:20,575 --> 00:23:22,575
You don't want me?

255
00:23:28,083 --> 00:23:30,083
No.

256
00:23:32,879 --> 00:23:36,298
That changes things a lot.

257
00:23:37,801 --> 00:23:40,521
But if it's not too much to ask,

258
00:23:42,055 --> 00:23:44,945
can you just promise me something?

259
00:23:46,893 --> 00:23:49,188
Don't do anything reckless.

260
00:23:51,815 --> 00:23:53,815
For Charlie's sake.

261
00:23:55,026 --> 00:23:57,971
And I’ll promise
