00:46:21,496 --> 00:46:23,496
Yeah. I guess I am.

519
00:46:24,166 --> 00:46:27,736
Well, it's just blood, Bella. No big deal.

520
00:46:32,340 --> 00:46:34,340
There.

521
00:46:40,182 --> 00:46:42,224
What are you staring at?

522
00:46:45,604 --> 00:46:47,730
You're sort of beautiful.

523
00:46:55,614 --> 00:46:58,249
How hard did you hit your head?

524
00:46:59,409 --> 00:47:01,409
I don't know.

525
00:47:02,829 --> 00:47:04,829
Let's go.

526
00:47:07,667 --> 00:47:09,569
I did see something in the woods.

527
00:47:09,669 --> 00:47:11,029
Totally. Baby, l believe you.

528
00:47:11,129 --> 00:47:14,741
No, he doesn't.
He's just trying to get lucky.

529
00:47:14,841 --> 00:47:18,844
No, okay. It was jet black and huge.

530
00:47:18,929 --> 00:47:21,748
On all fours, it was still taller than a person.

531
00:47:21,848 --> 00:47:22,999
A bear, maybe?

532
00:47:23,099 --> 00:47:26,878
Or an alien.
You're lucky you didn't get probed.

533
00:47:26,978 --> 00:47:28,979
Well, I saw it.

534
00:47:29,731 --> 00:47:32,467
You know, you're not the only one.

535
00:47:32,567 --> 00:47:35,178
My dad's been getting
reports at the station.

536
00:47:35,278 --> 00:47:38,181
Like, five hikers have been killed
by some bear.

537
00:47:38,281 --> 00:47:40,392
But they can't find the bear.

538
00:47:40,492 --> 00:47:42,492
Hmm.

539
00:47:43,578 --> 00:47:47,063
Last time you clowns doubt my girlfriend.

540
00:47:47,207 --> 00:47:49,207
Um...

541
00:47:50,585 --> 00:47:52,585
So? I mean,

542
00:47:52,879 --> 00:47:54,879
Bella's back?

543
00:47:58,301 --> 00:47:59,870
Yeah, I guess so.

544
00:47:59,970 --> 00:48:02,945
All right, that's... Well, welcome.

545
00:48:03,557 --> 00:48:06,787
So, listen, now that you're talking...

546
00:48:08,186 --> 00:48:14,731
...and eating again, which, you know,
you've got to get that protein in there,

547
00:48:14,943 --> 00:48:20,043
I was just wondering if you
wanted to go see a movie with me.

548
00:48:23,201 --> 00:48:25,828
Yeah. Sure. Yeah, l do.

549
00:48:27,706 --> 00:48:28,940
Cool.

550
00:48:29,040 --> 00:48:31,845
Let me see, we could check out...

551
00:48:32,127 --> 00:48:34,362
'Love Spelled Backwards Is Love'.

552
00:48:34,462 --> 00:48:37,532
You know, it's a dumb title,
but it's a romantic comedy.

553
00:48:37,632 --> 00:48:42,222
I mean, it's supposed to be pretty...
- No. No romance.

554
00:48:44,556 --> 00:48:48,466
How about 'Face Punch'?
Have you heard of that?

555
00:48:48,476 --> 00:48:50,879
I mean, that's an action movie.

556
00:48:50,979 --> 00:48:52,979
Yeah, that's perfect.

557
00:48:53,648 --> 00:48:55,648
Guns, adrenaline.

558
00:48:56,318 --> 00:48:57,552
That's my thing.

559
00:48:57,652 --> 00:48:59,054
Okay.

560
00:48:59,154 --> 00:49:03,475
We should get a bunch of people to go.
Do you guys want to go see 'Face Punch'?

561
00:49:03,575 --> 00:49:04,768
'Face Punch', yeah.

562
00:49:04,868 --> 00:49:06,353
Mike, hey, we were supposed to watch that.

563
00:49:06,453 --> 00:49:07,979
Remember, the trailer's like...

564
00:49:08,079 --> 00:49:10,273
'Punch faces.'
- I remember.

565
00:49:10,373 --> 00:49:13,083
Yeah. Movie night with Bella.

566
00:49:16,338 --> 00:49:18,338
So 'Face Punch', huh?

567
00:49:18,840 --> 00:49:20,841
You like action movies?

568
00:49:21,760 --> 00:49:23,760
Not really.

569
00:49:26,222 --> 00:49:29,016
I heard it sucks. Bad.

570
00:49:30,518 --> 00:49:34,088
Are you even old enough to see this movie?

571
00:49:34,356 --> 00:49:36,091
I mean, you know, without,
like, adult supervision.

572
00:49:36,191 --> 00:49:38,093
Right, yeah, well, she's
buying my ticket for me.

573
00:49:38,193 --> 00:49:40,193
She's buying it. Okay.

574
00:49:41,237 --> 00:49:44,182
Jessica bailed, and Angela
got the stomach flu,

575
00:49:44,282 --> 00:49:46,747
so Eric's taking care of her.

576
00:49:47,535 --> 00:49:50,000
It’s just us three.
- Great.

577
00:49:50,789 --> 00:49:52,789
Great.
- Yeah.

578
00:49:55,502 --> 00:49:56,778
Put your gun down.

579
00:49:56,878 --> 00:49:59,573
Put your gun down or I’m gonna
blow your frickin' head off.

580
00:49:59,673 --> 00:50:02,117
Both of you put both of your guns down...

581
00:50:02,217 --> 00:50:06,246
...or I’m gonna blow both
of your frickin' heads off.

582
00:50:06,346 --> 00:50:09,321
All right, forget it,
let's do this.

583
00:50:26,241 --> 00:50:29,216
Okay, I think I’m gonna throw up.

584
00:50:34,958 --> 00:50:36,526
He's...

585
00:50:36,626 --> 00:50:38,626
What a marshmallow.

586
00:50:39,587 --> 00:50:42,991
You should hold out for someone
with a stronger stomach.

587
00:50:43,091 --> 00:50:46,536
Someone who laughs at the gore
that makes weaker men vomit.

588
00:50:46,636 --> 00:50:49,951
Yeah. I’ll keep my eye open for that.

589
00:50:50,765 --> 00:50:55,525
I feel bad. He probably has
that flu that's going around.

590
00:50:58,440 --> 00:51:00,759
What? I can't hold your hand?

591
00:51:00,859 --> 00:51:02,901
No, of course you can.

592
00:51:05,739 --> 00:51:11,853
I just think it means, you know, something
a little different to you. So...

593
00:51:11,953 --> 00:51:16,118
Okay, well, tell me something.
You like me, right?

594
00:51:20,211 --> 00:51:23,441
And you think I’m sort of beautiful?

595
00:51:23,965 --> 00:51:27,593
Jacob, please, don't do this.

596
00:51:34,350 --> 00:51:36,350
Why?

597
00:51:38,897 --> 00:51:42,297
Because you're about to ruin everything.

598
00:51:43,526 --> 00:51:46,153
And I need you.

599
00:51:53,078 --> 00:51:55,713
Well, I’ve got loads of time.

600
00:51:56,664 --> 00:51:58,704
I’m not gonna give up.

601
00:51:59,709 --> 00:52:02,336
I don't want you to,

602
00:52:04,589 --> 00:52:09,009
but it's just 'cause I don't
want you to go anywhere.

603
00:52:10,345 --> 00:52:12,596
And that's really selfish.

604
00:52:16,101 --> 00:52:20,351
You know, I’m not like a
car that you can fix up.

605
00:52:23,483 --> 00:52:28,158
I’m never gonna run right.
So I should be fair to you.

606
00:52:29,948 --> 00:52:32,413
It’s because of him, right?

607
00:52:42,502 --> 00:52:44,502
Look,

608
00:52:45,380 --> 00:52:47,798
I know what he did to you.

609
00:52:49,175 --> 00:52:53,387
But, Bella, l would never ever do that.

610
00:52:56,099 --> 00:52:59,309
I won't ever hurt you. l promise.

611
00:53:00,812 --> 00:53:02,812
I won't let you down.

612
00:53:03,690 --> 00:53:05,690
You can count on me.

613
00:53:13,408 --> 00:53:15,408
Well,

614
00:53:19,831 --> 00:53:21,831
I need to go home.

615
00:53:28,715 --> 00:53:32,285
I was feeling sick before the movie. Okay?

616
00:53:34,804 --> 00:53:36,122
What is your problem?

617
00:53:36,222 --> 00:53:38,687
Right now? You're my problem.

618
00:53:39,142 --> 00:53:43,392
Feeling sick?
Maybe you need to go to the hospital.

619
00:53:43,605 --> 00:53:45,423
You want me to put you in the hospital?

620
00:53:45,523 --> 00:53:49,177
Jake. Jake. Jake, the movie's over.
What are you doing?

621
00:53:49,277 --> 00:53:51,904
You're really hot.

622
00:53:53,448 --> 00:53:57,698
Like, you feel like you have a fever.
Are you okay?

623
00:53:57,744 --> 00:54:00,294
I don't know what's happening.

624
00:54:01,998 --> 00:54:03,998
I gotta go.

625
00:54:08,588 --> 00:54:10,588
That dude is weird.

626
00:54:13,801 --> 00:54:16,691
Jake, your dad says you have mono.

627
00:54:17,055 --> 00:54:20,795
He won't let me visit,
but would you call me?

628
00:54:25,772 --> 00:54:28,398
Hey, it's me again. I just...

629
00:54:29,442 --> 00:54:33,346
I’m sorry about what I said
at the movie theatre.

630
00:54:33,446 --> 00:54:37,526
I just wanted to hear your
voice, so no pressure.

631
00:54:39,786 --> 00:54:41,786
Jacob, please...

632
00:54:43,164 --> 00:54:44,524
Call me.

633
00:54:44,624 --> 00:54:47,684
Okay. We should be back around 3:00.

634
00:54:54,300 --> 00:54:56,300
Hey.

635
00:54:56,386 --> 00:54:58,371
Look, l don't have to go fishing today.

636
00:54:58,471 --> 00:55:00,165
Yes, you do.

637
00:55:00,265 --> 00:55:02,876
Yeah, you do. Go.
What are you talking about?

638
00:55:02,976 --> 00:55:04,627
Just be careful.

639
00:55:04,727 --> 00:55:06,727
Always am.

640
00:55:07,855 --> 00:55:10,341
Those bears won't get
the drop on me, Bella.

641
00:55:10,441 --> 00:55:12,442
My Kung Fu is strong.

642
00:55:45,685 --> 00:55:47,685
Jake.

643
00:55:47,854 --> 00:55:49,854
Hey.

644
00:55:53,943 --> 00:55:55,943
You cut your hair off?

645
00:55:58,740 --> 00:56:00,740
And got a tattoo?

646
00:56:03,911 --> 00:56:05,104
Bella.

647
00:56:05,204 --> 00:56:08,983
l thought you were too
sick to come outside...

648
00:56:09,083 --> 00:56:12,143
...or pick up the phone when l call.

649
00:56:13,046 --> 00:56:15,046
Go away.

650
00:56:15,715 --> 00:56:17,715
What?

651
00:56:18,551 --> 00:56:20,551
Go away.

652
00:56:21,846 --> 00:56:23,998
What happened to you? What's...

653
00:56:24,098 --> 00:56:26,391
Hey. What happened?

654
00:56:29,354 --> 00:56:32,382
Did Sam get to you?
Is that what's happening?

655
00:56:32,482 --> 00:56:35,967
Sam's trying to help me. Don't blame him.

656
00:56:36,903 --> 00:56:39,430
But if you want somebody to blame,

657
00:56:39,530 --> 00:56:44,375
how about those filthy bloodsuckers
you love, the Cullen’s?

658
00:56:50,666 --> 00:56:51,776
l don't know what you're talking about.

659
00:56:51,876 --> 00:56:54,570
No, you know exactly
what I’m talking about.

660
00:56:54,670 --> 00:56:57,985
You've been lying to everyone. Charlie.

661
00:56:59,759 --> 00:57:01,802
But you can't lie to me.

662
00:57:02,887 --> 00:57:05,182
Not anymore, Bella.
- Jacob.

663
00:57:05,723 --> 00:57:07,723
Jacob.

664
00:57:13,106 --> 00:57:15,106
Look, Bella,

665
00:57:15,817 --> 00:57:18,197
we can't be friends anymore.

666
00:57:19,028 --> 00:57:23,023
Look, Jake, l know that
I’ve been hurting you.

667
00:57:24,492 --> 00:57:27,494
It’s killing me. It kills me.

668
00:57:29,789 --> 00:57:32,567
l just need... Maybe give me, like,

669
00:57:32,667 --> 00:57:35,528
some time or something.
- Look, don't.

670
00:57:35,628 --> 00:57:37,628
It’s not you.

671
00:57:40,049 --> 00:57:43,364
It’s not you, it's me, right? Really?

672
00:57:43,886 --> 00:57:46,221
It’s true. It is me.

673
00:57:49,183 --> 00:57:51,309
I’m not good.

674
00:57:54,105 --> 00:57:57,315
l used to be a good kid.

675
00:57:58,651 --> 00:58:00,651
Not anymore.

676
00:58:01,195 --> 00:58:04,015
This doesn't even matter. All right?

677
00:58:04,115 --> 00:58:05,099
This is over.

678
00:58:05,199 --> 00:58:07,494
You can't break up with me.

679
00:58:09,287 --> 00:58:11,287
l mean...

680
00:58:11,956 --> 00:58:14,761
...l mean, you're my best friend.

681
00:58:16,711 --> 00:58:18,711
You promised me.

682
00:58:19,922 --> 00:58:21,922
l know.

683
00:58:22,091 --> 00:58:25,321
l promised l wouldn't hurt you, Bella,

684
00:58:25,678 --> 00:58:28,738
and this is me keeping that promise.

685
00:58:29,015 --> 00:58:31,015
Go home...

686
00:58:31,058 --> 00:58:35,053
...and don't come back
or you're gonna get hurt.

687
00:58:48,034 --> 00:58:50,034
Alice,

688
00:58:50,411 --> 00:58:52,411
things are...

689
00:58:53,539 --> 00:58:55,539
Things are bad again.

690
00:58:56,626 --> 00:59:00,111
Without Jake, l just... l can't stand it.

691
00:59:03,090 --> 00:59:05,385
l don't see Edward anymore.

692
00:59:06,844 --> 00:59:10,414
Will it really feel like he never existed?

693
00:59:17,271 --> 00:59:21,266
l will find the place
where l can see him again.

694
01:00:15,705 --> 01:00:17,705
Bella.

695
01:00:17,957 --> 01:00:19,957
Laurent.

696
01:00:21,210 --> 01:00:24,015
l didn't expect to find you here.

697
01:00:25,840 --> 01:00:30,176
l went to visit the Cullen’s,
but the house is empty.

698
01:00:32,513 --> 01:00:35,124
I’m surprised they left you behind.

699
01:00:35,224 --> 01:00:37,225
Weren't you sort of...

700
01:00:38,352 --> 01:00:40,352
...a pet of theirs?

701
01:00:40,938 --> 01:00:42,465
Yeah. You could say that.

702
01:00:42,565 --> 01:00:44,899
Do the Cullen’s visit often?

703
01:00:50,114 --> 01:00:52,114
Lie.

704
01:00:56,704 --> 01:00:57,980
Yeah, absolutely, all the time.

705
01:00:58,080 --> 01:00:59,607
Lie better.

706
01:00:59,707 --> 01:01:02,852
I’ll tell them that you stopped by.

707
01:01:02,918 --> 01:01:05,213
But l probably shouldn't...

708
01:01:05,588 --> 01:01:08,256
...tell Edward,

709
01:01:10,051 --> 01:01:11,410
'cause he's pretty protective.

710
01:01:11,510 --> 01:01:13,890
But he's far away, isn't he?

711
01:01:16,599 --> 01:01:18,334
Why are you here?

712
01:01:18,434 --> 01:01:22,812
I came as a favour to Victoria.

713
01:01:26,275 --> 01:01:27,802
Victoria?
- She asked me to see...

714
01:01:27,902 --> 01:01:31,472
...if you were still under
the protection of the Cullen’s.

715
01:01:31,572 --> 01:01:35,434
Victoria feels it's only fair
to kill Edward's mate,

716
01:01:35,534 --> 01:01:37,186
given he killed hers.

717
01:01:37,286 --> 01:01:39,286
An eye for an eye.

718
01:01:39,747 --> 01:01:40,898
Threaten him.

719
01:01:40,998 --> 01:01:45,503
Edward would know who did it.
And he'd come after you.

720
01:01:45,544 --> 01:01:47,544
l don't think he will.

721
01:01:48,673 --> 01:01:51,993
After all, how much
could you mean to him...

722
01:01:52,093 --> 01:01:55,068
...if he left you here unprotected?

723
01:01:56,931 --> 01:01:59,917
Victoria won't be happy
about my killing you,

724
01:02:00,017 --> 01:02:02,057
but l can't help myself.

725
01:02:02,311 --> 01:02:04,046
You are so mouth-watering.

726
01:02:04,146 --> 01:02:08,736
Please, don't. l mean, you helped us.
- No, no, no, no.

727
01:02:09,068 --> 01:02:12,513
Don't be afraid. I’m doing you a kindness.

728
01:02:12,613 --> 01:02:15,758
Victoria plans on killing you slowly,

729
01:02:16,575 --> 01:02:18,575
painfully,

730
01:02:18,869 --> 01:02:21,334
whereas I’ll make it quick.

731
01:02:21,455 --> 01:02:23,455
l promise.

732
01:02:23,833 --> 01:02:25,834
You will feel nothing.

733
01:02:31,590 --> 01:02:33,590
Edward, l love you.

734
01:02:35,594 --> 01:02:37,594
l don't believe it.

735
01:03:44,330 --> 01:03:46,857
Dad. l saw them.
- What's the matter?

736
01:03:46,957 --> 01:03:49,944
In the woods. They're not bears.
- What do you mean 'in the woods'?

737
01:03:50,044 --> 01:03:51,779
Bell, what the hell were you
doing out in the woods?

738
01:03:51,879 --> 01:03:55,574
They're wolves.
l mean, they're like huge wolves.

739
01:03:55,674 --> 01:03:57,493
Are you sure about that, Bella?

740
01:03:57,593 --> 01:04:01,673
Yeah. l just saw them.
They were after something.

741
01:04:02,014 --> 01:04:04,014
Wolves?

742
01:04:04,391 --> 01:04:06,391
You saw them?

743
01:04:08,521 --> 01:04:11,064
All right, well, Harry,

744
01:04:12,358 --> 01:04:16,053
feel like going hunting?
Get some of your guys together?

745
01:04:16,153 --> 01:04:18,363
Sure, yeah, I’ll just...

746
01:04:19,949 --> 01:04:22,839
By now, those wolves will be dead,

747
01:04:23,410 --> 01:04:26,439
and Laurent would have
told her I’m unprotected.

748
01:04:26,539 --> 01:04:28,539
Victoria.

749
01:04:29,542 --> 01:04:30,985
l should go to the station.

750
01:04:31,085 --> 01:04:33,805
Yeah, you should. You should go.

751
01:04:34,171 --> 01:04:36,806
Can you just stay in the house?

752
01:05:01,574 --> 01:05:03,574
Bella.

753
01:05:05,494 --> 01:05:06,896
You scared me.

754
01:05:06,996 --> 01:05:11,671
What the hell are you doing?
- Back up. I’m coming up.

755
01:05:22,720 --> 01:05:24,720
Hey.

756
01:05:26,098 --> 01:05:28,098
Look, I’m sorry.

757
01:05:34,857 --> 01:05:37,134
For what?
- l wish l could explain.

758
01:05:37,234 --> 01:05:40,361
But l literally can't.

759
01:05:49,121 --> 01:05:53,317
Have you ever had a secret
you couldn't tell anyone,

760
01:05:53,417 --> 01:05:56,052
one that wasn't yours to share?

761
01:05:58,797 --> 01:06:01,492
Well, that's what it's like for me.

762
01:06:01,592 --> 01:06:03,592
But worse.

763
01:06:04,303 --> 01:06:07,680
You have no idea how tight I’m bound.

764
01:06:08,849 --> 01:06:10,849
l hate this.

765
01:06:11,226 --> 01:06:13,946
l hate what they've done to you.

766
01:06:27,701 --> 01:06:31,526
l mean, the killer part is, you already know.

767
01:06:34,875 --> 01:06:40,060
Bella, do you remember when we
walked on the beach at La Push?

768
01:06:41,131 --> 01:06:43,131
The...

769
01:06:46,428 --> 01:06:49,097
The story. The story about...

770
01:06:50,391 --> 01:06:52,391
...the cold ones.

771
01:06:53,769 --> 01:06:58,699
l guess l understand why that's
the only part you remember.

772
01:07:04,530 --> 01:07:08,366
There's gotta be something
that you can do.

773
01:07:08,450 --> 01:07:10,575
No. I’m in it for life.

774
01:07:11,912 --> 01:07:14,523
Well, maybe we should just
get out of here for a while.

775
01:07:14,623 --> 01:07:16,483
Just leave,

776
01:07:16,583 --> 01:07:18,583
just you and me.

777
01:07:18,627 --> 01:07:20,627
You'd do that?

778
01:07:23,382 --> 01:07:25,382
l would do it for you.

