who tried to kill Bella because of you.

1022
01:29:04,307 --> 01:29:05,333
Victoria?

1023
01:29:05,433 --> 01:29:07,543
Yeah, Victoria's been around.

1024
01:29:07,643 --> 01:29:09,643
l didn't see her.

1025
01:29:09,895 --> 01:29:14,315
l didn't see you get pulled
out of the water, either.

1026
01:29:14,358 --> 01:29:17,303
l can't see past you and your pack of mutts.

1027
01:29:17,403 --> 01:29:19,529
Don't get me upset...

1028
01:29:19,613 --> 01:29:25,733
Hey, stop. Stop, stop, stop, stop.
- ...or things are gonna get very ugly.

1029
01:29:29,165 --> 01:29:31,290
I’ll give you a minute.

1030
01:29:37,089 --> 01:29:39,089
Hey.

1031
01:29:39,258 --> 01:29:41,827
You're not going anywhere.
You're gonna come back,

1032
01:29:41,927 --> 01:29:45,242
right?
- As soon as you put the dog out.

1033
01:29:53,731 --> 01:29:55,731
Is he...

1034
01:29:59,236 --> 01:30:00,763
Are there others?
How many Cullen’s are here...

1035
01:30:00,863 --> 01:30:03,015
...and how long are they staying?

1036
01:30:03,115 --> 01:30:05,115
No.

1037
01:30:05,117 --> 01:30:07,117
It’s just Alice.

1038
01:30:11,499 --> 01:30:14,814
And she can stay as long as she'd like.

1039
01:30:16,754 --> 01:30:19,389
Well, are the rest coming back?

1040
01:30:25,388 --> 01:30:27,388
No.

1041
01:30:28,307 --> 01:30:30,307
Not that l know of.

1042
01:30:30,935 --> 01:30:32,935
Anything else?

1043
01:30:36,774 --> 01:30:38,774
That's it.

1044
01:30:40,319 --> 01:30:45,164
Well, if that's all, then you'd
better go run back to Sam.

1045
01:30:47,076 --> 01:30:49,076
I’ve done it again.

1046
01:30:49,829 --> 01:30:52,124
l keep breaking my promise.

1047
01:30:57,253 --> 01:31:00,568
We don't have to do this to each other.

1048
01:31:04,468 --> 01:31:06,468
Yes, we do.

1049
01:31:17,857 --> 01:31:19,857
Bella...

1050
01:31:42,089 --> 01:31:44,089
Swan residence.

1051
01:31:49,472 --> 01:31:51,556
He's not here right now.

1052
01:31:52,266 --> 01:31:54,391
He's arranging a funeral.

1053
01:32:10,117 --> 01:32:11,936
Who was that?

1054
01:32:12,036 --> 01:32:13,062
What?

1055
01:32:13,162 --> 01:32:15,162
Always in the way.

1056
01:32:17,124 --> 01:32:18,317
Who was that?

1057
01:32:18,417 --> 01:32:20,027
Bella, step back.

1058
01:32:20,127 --> 01:32:23,823
Jake, who was that?
- Bella. Bella, it's Edward.

1059
01:32:23,923 --> 01:32:28,598
He thinks you're dead.
Rosalie told him why l came here.

1060
01:32:29,553 --> 01:32:32,248
Why would you...
Why didn't you let me speak to him?

1061
01:32:32,348 --> 01:32:33,499
He didn't ask for you.
- Bella.

1062
01:32:33,599 --> 01:32:37,753
l don't care.
- Bella. Bella. He's going to the Volturi.

1063
01:32:37,853 --> 01:32:39,853
He wants to die, too.

1064
01:32:41,690 --> 01:32:44,802
He left you, Bella.
He didn't want you anymore. Remember?

1065
01:32:44,902 --> 01:32:48,973
No, I’m not gonna let him
kill himself out of guilt.

1066
01:32:49,073 --> 01:32:51,073
What about your dad?

1067
01:32:51,450 --> 01:32:55,955
I’m 18. I’m legally free
to go, and l left a note.

1068
01:32:56,622 --> 01:32:58,622
Please, Bella,

1069
01:32:59,792 --> 01:33:01,876
just stay here.

1070
01:33:03,629 --> 01:33:05,629
For Charlie.

1071
01:33:07,967 --> 01:33:09,967
Or for me.

1072
01:33:10,553 --> 01:33:12,553
l have to go.

1073
01:33:18,060 --> 01:33:20,060
I’m begging you.

1074
01:33:22,481 --> 01:33:24,481
Please.

1075
01:33:25,609 --> 01:33:27,609
Goodbye, Jacob.

1076
01:33:35,744 --> 01:33:37,744
Okay.

1077
01:34:38,390 --> 01:34:40,855
So you've made up your minds.

1078
01:34:40,976 --> 01:34:44,121
I’m afraid your particular gifts...

1079
01:34:44,563 --> 01:34:47,198
...are too valuable to destroy.

1080
01:34:47,858 --> 01:34:52,737
But if you're unhappy with your lot, join us.

1081
01:34:53,864 --> 01:34:57,689
We would be delighted to utilize your skills.

1082
01:34:58,535 --> 01:35:01,510
Won't you consider staying with us?

1083
01:35:02,873 --> 01:35:05,192
You know it will happen anyway.

1084
01:35:05,292 --> 01:35:07,292
Not without cause.

1085
01:35:11,465 --> 01:35:13,465
Such a waste.

1086
01:35:20,265 --> 01:35:22,042
I’m guessing you didn't rent this car?

1087
01:35:22,142 --> 01:35:24,169
l figured you wouldn't be
opposed to grand theft auto.

1088
01:35:24,269 --> 01:35:26,269
Not today.

1089
01:35:28,982 --> 01:35:30,634
What? What do you see?

1090
01:35:30,734 --> 01:35:32,595
They refused him.

1091
01:35:32,695 --> 01:35:35,160
So?
- He's gonna make a scene.

1092
01:35:35,447 --> 01:35:38,677
Show himself to the humans.
- No. When?

1093
01:35:39,326 --> 01:35:44,171
He's gonna wait until noon,
when the sun's at its highest.

1094
01:35:45,124 --> 01:35:46,317
God, Alice, you got to hurry up.

1095
01:35:46,417 --> 01:35:48,417
There's Volterra.

1096
01:36:13,068 --> 01:36:15,888
Why are they all in red?
- San Marco's Day festival.

1097
01:36:15,988 --> 01:36:18,766
They're commemorating the expulsion
of vampires from the city.

1098
01:36:18,866 --> 01:36:20,184
It’s the perfect setting.

1099
01:36:20,284 --> 01:36:22,811
The Volturi will never let him get
far enough to reveal himself.

1100
01:36:22,911 --> 01:36:24,605
We have five minutes.

1101
01:36:24,705 --> 01:36:27,085
l know, Bella, just breathe.

1102
01:36:33,088 --> 01:36:34,073
Alice.

1103
01:36:34,173 --> 01:36:36,325
Bella, you're the only
one he can't see coming.

1104
01:36:36,425 --> 01:36:40,162
lf l go, he'll read my thoughts.
He'll think I’m lying. He'll rush into it.

1105
01:36:40,262 --> 01:36:44,597
Where do l go?
- He'll be under the clock tower. Go.

1106
01:38:36,044 --> 01:38:38,044
Don't.

1107
01:38:39,464 --> 01:38:40,574
Heaven.

1108
01:38:40,674 --> 01:38:42,674
You have to move.

1109
01:38:43,176 --> 01:38:46,576
Open your eyes. Look at me. I’m alive.

1110
01:38:46,722 --> 01:38:48,722
You have to move.

1111
01:38:49,308 --> 01:38:51,308
Bella.

1112
01:38:58,025 --> 01:39:00,151
You're here.
- I’m here.

1113
01:39:02,988 --> 01:39:04,988
You're alive.

1114
01:39:07,659 --> 01:39:09,659
Yes.

1115
01:39:18,337 --> 01:39:21,142
l needed to make you see me once.

1116
01:39:21,965 --> 01:39:23,242
You had to know that l was alive,

1117
01:39:23,342 --> 01:39:27,592
that you didn't have to
feel guilty about anything.

1118
01:39:29,348 --> 01:39:31,933
l can let you go now.

1119
01:39:36,688 --> 01:39:38,983
l never acted out of guilt.

1120
01:39:41,318 --> 01:39:45,823
l just couldn't live in a
world where you don't exist.

1121
01:39:46,198 --> 01:39:48,240
But you said...
- l lied.

1122
01:39:48,951 --> 01:39:52,606
l had to lie.
But you believed me so easily.

1123
01:39:57,709 --> 01:40:01,789
Because it doesn't make
sense for you to love me.

1124
01:40:04,007 --> 01:40:08,257
l mean, I’m nothing.
I’m human. I’m nothing.

1125
01:40:08,804 --> 01:40:12,390
Bella, you're everything to me.

1126
01:40:14,351 --> 01:40:16,351
You're everything.

1127
01:40:41,753 --> 01:40:43,822
l won't be needing your
services after all, gentlemen.

1128
01:40:43,922 --> 01:40:45,991
Aro wants to speak with you again.

1129
01:40:46,091 --> 01:40:47,326
No rules were broken.

1130
01:40:47,426 --> 01:40:51,580
Nonetheless, we should take this
conversation to a more appropriate venue.

1131
01:40:51,680 --> 01:40:53,680
Fine.

1132
01:40:54,266 --> 01:40:56,585
Bella, why don't you go and
enjoy the rest of the festival?

1133
01:40:56,685 --> 01:40:58,003
The girl comes with us.

1134
01:40:58,103 --> 01:41:00,103
No. You can go to hell.

1135
01:41:02,190 --> 01:41:03,926
Come on, guys.

1136
01:41:04,026 --> 01:41:08,180
It’s a festival.
You wouldn't want to make a scene.

1137
01:41:08,280 --> 01:41:09,973
We wouldn't.

1138
01:41:10,073 --> 01:41:12,073
Enough.

1139
01:41:12,951 --> 01:41:14,811
Jane.

1140
01:41:14,911 --> 01:41:18,566
Aro sent me to see what
was taking so long.

1141
01:41:25,964 --> 01:41:27,964
Just do as she says.

1142
01:41:40,479 --> 01:41:42,479
Go ahead.

1143
01:41:45,859 --> 01:41:47,859
Don't be scared.

1144
01:41:48,487 --> 01:41:50,487
Are you?

1145
01:41:50,781 --> 01:41:52,781
No.

1146
01:42:30,445 --> 01:42:32,571
Is she human?
- Yes.

1147
01:42:35,742 --> 01:42:37,742
Does she know?

1148
01:42:37,869 --> 01:42:39,271
Yes.

1149
01:42:39,371 --> 01:42:41,371
Then, why would...

1150
01:42:42,791 --> 01:42:44,791
She wants to be.

1151
01:42:45,043 --> 01:42:46,445
And so she will be.

1152
01:42:46,545 --> 01:42:48,545
Or dessert.

1153
01:42:56,471 --> 01:43:00,917
Sister. They send you out to get
one and you bring back two.

1154
01:43:01,017 --> 01:43:03,017
And a half.

1155
01:43:03,645 --> 01:43:05,005
Such a clever girl.

1156
01:43:05,105 --> 01:43:07,105
What a happy surprise.

1157
01:43:08,066 --> 01:43:10,734
Bella is alive after all.

1158
01:43:11,611 --> 01:43:14,280
Isn't that wonderful?

1159
01:43:15,407 --> 01:43:17,407
l love a happy ending.

1160
01:43:18,410 --> 01:43:20,410
Ah.

1161
01:43:21,746 --> 01:43:23,746
They are so rare.

1162
01:43:30,422 --> 01:43:33,397
Her blood appeals to you so much...

1163
01:43:34,217 --> 01:43:36,217
...it makes me thirsty.

1164
01:43:36,303 --> 01:43:39,164
How can you stand to be so close to her?

1165
01:43:39,264 --> 01:43:43,684
It’s not without difficulty.
- Yes, l can see that.

1166
01:43:45,687 --> 01:43:50,175
Aro can read every thought
I’ve ever had with one touch.

1167
01:43:50,275 --> 01:43:52,655
And now you know everything.

1168
01:43:53,111 --> 01:43:55,111
So get on with it.

1169
01:43:58,033 --> 01:44:01,773
You are quite a soul
reader yourself, Edward.

1170
01:44:02,871 --> 01:44:07,124
Though you can't read Bella's thoughts.

1171
01:44:10,545 --> 01:44:12,545
Fascinating.

1172
01:44:15,550 --> 01:44:20,990
l would love to see if you are an
exception to my gifts, as well.

1173
01:44:23,642 --> 01:44:25,852
Would you do me the honour?

1174
01:44:46,665 --> 01:44:48,358
Interesting.

1175
01:44:48,458 --> 01:44:50,152
Hmm.

1176
01:44:50,252 --> 01:44:52,252
l see nothing.

1177
01:45:01,179 --> 01:45:03,179
l wonder if...

1178
01:45:03,556 --> 01:45:07,296
Let us see if she's
immune to all our powers.

1179
01:45:08,103 --> 01:45:10,103
Shall we, Jane?

1180
01:45:11,439 --> 01:45:13,439
No.
- Pain.

1181
01:45:29,207 --> 01:45:31,207
Stop.

1182
01:45:31,376 --> 01:45:33,111
Stop. Please. Stop.

1183
01:45:33,211 --> 01:45:37,047
Stop. Just stop hurting him.
Please. Please.

1184
01:45:38,758 --> 01:45:40,758
Jane?

1185
01:45:42,095 --> 01:45:44,095
Master?

1186
01:45:47,684 --> 01:45:49,684
Go ahead, my dear.

1187
01:45:54,899 --> 01:45:57,279
This may hurt just a little.

1188
01:46:13,251 --> 01:46:15,251
Remarkable.

1189
01:46:16,963 --> 01:46:19,214
She confounds us all.

1190
01:46:20,258 --> 01:46:23,427
So what do we do with you now?

1191
01:46:23,970 --> 01:46:27,795
You already know what
you're going to do, Aro.

1192
01:46:28,099 --> 01:46:30,099
She knows too much.

1193
01:46:30,477 --> 01:46:32,477
She's a liability.

1194
01:46:33,605 --> 01:46:35,605
Hmm.

1195
01:46:36,232 --> 01:46:38,232
That's true.

1196
01:46:41,654 --> 01:46:43,654
Felix?

1197
01:46:46,826 --> 01:46:48,826
No.

1198
01:47:49,472 --> 01:47:52,558
Please. No. No. Please, please.

1199
01:47:55,437 --> 01:47:58,564
Kill me. Kill me. Not him.

1200
01:48:09,576 --> 01:48:12,119
How extraordinary.

1201
01:48:13,830 --> 01:48:18,250
You would give up your
life for someone like us.

1202
01:48:19,377 --> 01:48:21,377
A vampire.

1203
01:48:22,130 --> 01:48:24,548
A soulless monster.

1204
01:48:24,632 --> 01:48:26,633
Just get away from her.

1205
01:48:30,722 --> 01:48:35,184
You don't know a thing about his soul.

1206
01:48:46,779 --> 01:48:48,779
This is a sadness.

1207
01:48:50,617 --> 01:48:55,207
lf only it were your intention
to give her immortality.

1208
01:49:03,087 --> 01:49:05,087
Wait.

1209
01:49:06,007 --> 01:49:08,091
Bella will be one of us.

1210
01:49:09,802 --> 01:49:11,802
I’ve seen it.

1211
01:49:13,097 --> 01:49:15,222
I’ll change her myself.

1212
01:49:48,925 --> 01:49:50,743
Mesmerizing.

1213
01:49:50,843 --> 01:49:55,264
To see what you have seen
before it has happened.

1214
01:49:58,184 --> 01:50:02,646
Your gifts will make for an intriguing...

1215
01:50:03,898 --> 01:50:05,898
...immortal,

1216
01:50:06,401 --> 01:50:08,401
Isabella.

1217
01:50:12,824 --> 01:50:14,824
Go now.

1218
01:50:14,951 --> 01:50:16,951
Make your preparations.

1219
01:50:17,704 --> 01:50:19,829
Let us be done with this.

1220
01:50:21,541 --> 01:50:24,006
Heidi will arrive any moment.

1221
01:50:25,670 --> 01:50:29,089
Thank you for your visit.

1222
01:50:29,173 --> 01:50:30,700
We will return the favour.

1223
01:50:30,800 --> 01:50:33,745
l would advise that you follow
through on your promise soon.

1224
01:50:33,845 --> 01:50:36,480
We do not offer second chances.

1225
01:50:37,849 --> 01:50:40,934
Goodbye, my young friends.

1226
01:50:47,317 --> 01:50:49,093
Nice fishing, Heidi.

1227
01:50:49,193 --> 01:50:51,429
Yes, they do look rather juicy.

1228
01:50:51,529 --> 01:50:53,529
Save some for me.

1229
01:50:54,198 --> 01:50:57,034
This way, please. Stay together.

1230
01:51:11,674 --> 01:51:13,674
Stop. Stop.

1231
01:51:24,062 --> 01:51:26,062
You're here.

1232
01:51:27,649 --> 01:51:29,649
You can sleep.

1233
01:51:33,029 --> 01:51:36,259
I’ll still be here when you wake up.

1234
01:51:39,243 --> 01:51:42,287
Bella, the only reason l left...

1235
01:51:44,082 --> 01:51:47,907
...was because l thought
l was protecting you.

1236
01:51:48,878 --> 01:51:50,488
l needed you...

1237
01:51:50,588 --> 01:51:54,549
...to have a chance at a normal, happy life.

1238
01:51:58,638 --> 01:52:01,358
It was so easy for you to leave.

1239
01:52:03,601 --> 01:52:08,531
Leaving you was the hardest
thing I’ve done in 100 years.

1240
01:52:14,070 --> 01:52:16,070
And l swear,

1241
01:52:16,948 --> 01:52:19,616
l will never fail you again.

1242
01:52:21,911 --> 01:52:23,911
I’m so sorry.

1243
01:52:25,873 --> 01:52:27,873
Charlie's coming.
- Hey.

1244
01:52:30,962 --> 01:52:32,962
You okay?

1245
01:52:33,756 --> 01:52:35,756
I’m fine.

1246
01:52:38,136 --> 01:52:40,601
Dad, you don't have to worry.

1247
01:52:40,805 --> 01:52:42,790
You know, last time you
said that, you took off.

1248
01:52:42,890 --> 01:52:45,610
l didn't see you for three days.

1249
01:52:46,769 --> 01:52:48,809
I’m really sorry, Dad.

1250
01:52:50,440 --> 01:52:54,151
Bella, do not ever do that to me again.

1251
01:52:56,988 --> 01:52:58,988
Ever.

1252
01:53:00,867 --> 01:53:02,867
And you're grounded...

1253
01:53:02,910 --> 01:53:05,375
...for the rest of your life.

1254
01:53:06,205 --> 01:53:08,205
Okay.

1255
01:53:17,675 --> 01:53:21,670
I’m not technically
breaking any of his rules.

1256
01:53:23,473 --> 01:53:27,085
He did say l couldn't take
a step inside the door.

1257
01:53:27,185 --> 01:53:29,650
l came in through the window.

1258
01:53:33,107 --> 01:53:35,912
He's not gonna forgive me easily.

1259
01:53:38,070 --> 01:53:40,070
l know.

1260
01:53:41,407 --> 01:53:43,407
Can you?

1261
01:53:46,537 --> 01:53:48,537
l hope you can,

1262
01:53:48,915 --> 01:53:53,335
'cause l honestly don't know
how to live without you.

1263
01:53:56,464 --> 01:53:58,464
Come here.

1264
01:54:15,525 --> 01:54:18,485
Once Alice changes me,

1265
01:54:21,405 --> 01:54:23,573
you can't get rid of me.

1266
01:54:24,784 --> 01:54:27,249
She won't need to change you.

1267
01:54:27,703 --> 01:54:32,208
There are always ways to keep
the Volturi in the dark.

1268
01:54:32,917 --> 01:54:35,293
No. No.

1269
01:54:42,093 --> 01:54:44,218
You all know what l want.

1270
01:54:46,264 --> 01:54:49,409
And l know how much I’m asking for.

1271
01:54:51,519 --> 01:54:55,006
The only thing that l can think of
for it to be fair is to just vote.

1272
01:54:55,106 --> 01:54:59,441
You don't know what you're talking about.
- Shut up.

1273
01:55:00,069 --> 01:55:01,637
Alice?

1274
01:55:01,737 --> 01:55:04,542
l already consider you my sister.

1275
01:55:08,077 --> 01:55:09,687
Yes.
- Thank you.

1276
01:55:09,787 --> 01:55:11,787
l vote 'yes.'

1277
01:55:12,707 --> 01:55:17,212
It would be nice to not want
to kill you all the time.

1278
01:55:18,087 --> 01:55:19,113
Hmm.

1279
01:55:19,213 --> 01:55:21,213
I’m sorry.

1280
01:55:22,466 --> 01:55:26,120
I’m really sorry to both
of you for how I've acted,

1281
01:55:26,220 --> 01:55:28,247
and I’m really grateful
that you were brave enough...

1282
01:55:28,347 --> 01:55:30,812
...to go and save my brother.

1283
01:55:31,976 --> 01:55:36,396
But this isn't a life l would
have chosen for myself.

1284
01:55:37,982 --> 01:55:42,742
And l wish that there'd been
someone to vote 'no' for me.

1285
01:55:44,530 --> 01:55:46,530
So, no.

1286
01:55:47,366 --> 01:55:49,366
I vote 'Hell yeah.'

1287
01:55:51,162 --> 01:55:53,523
And we can pick a fight with
these Volturi some other way.

1288
01:55:53,623 --> 01:55:57,109
I already consider you a part of the family.

1289
01:55:57,209 --> 01:55:59,209
Yes.

1290
01:56:04,342 --> 01:56:06,807
Why are you doing this to me?

1291
01:56:08,262 --> 01:56:09,580
You know what this means.

1292
01:56:09,680 --> 01:56:14,210
You've chosen not to live without
her, which leaves me no choice.

1293
01:56:14,310 --> 01:56:16,310
I won't lose my son.

1294
01:56:22,401 --> 01:56:27,756
I’ll wait until after graduation
to make it easier on Charlie.

1295
01:56:31,452 --> 01:56:35,022
Edward, I want you to be the one to do it.

1296
01:56:41,379 --> 01:56:43,463
He wants to talk to me.

1297
01:56:46,592 --> 01:56:48,202
So you're still alive for now.

1298
01:56:48,302 --> 01:56:50,746
He thinks it's me keeping you away.

1299
01:56:50,846 --> 01:56:53,651
You stay the hell out of my head.

1300
01:56:54,433 --> 01:56:58,258
Jacob, I know you have
something to say to me.

1301
01:57:00,272 --> 01:57:05,219
But l want to say something to
you first, if that's all right.

1302
01:57:05,319 --> 01:57:07,319
Thank you.

1303
01:57:09,865 --> 01:57:13,686
Thank you for keeping Bella
alive when I didn't.

1304
01:57:13,786 --> 01:57:15,912
No. You didn't.

1305
01:57:17,915 --> 01:57:20,526
And it wasn't for your benefit, trust me.

1306
01:57:20,626 --> 01:57:22,626
I’m still grateful.

1307
01:57:23,087 --> 01:57:24,280
But I’m here now.

1308
01:57:24,380 --> 01:57:27,074
I’m not gonna leave her side
until she orders me away.

1309
01:57:27,174 --> 01:57:29,174
We'll see.

1310
01:57:31,387 --> 01:57:33,555
Hey, my turn to talk.

1311
01:57:38,102 --> 01:57:41,714
I’m here to remind you about
a key point in the treaty.

1312
01:57:41,814 --> 01:57:43,674
I haven't forgotten.

1313
01:57:43,774 --> 01:57:45,468
What key point?

1314
01:57:45,568 --> 01:57:48,033
lf any of them bites a human,

1315
01:57:48,612 --> 01:57:50,612
the truce is over.

1316
01:57:51,782 --> 01:57:53,601
But if I choose it, it has
nothing to do with you.

1317
01:57:53,701 --> 01:57:55,744
No. No, I won't let you.

1318
01:57:57,329 --> 01:57:59,732
You're not gonna be one of them, Bella.

1319
01:57:59,832 --> 01:58:01,832
It’s not up to you.

1320
01:58:02,460 --> 01:58:04,779
You know what we'll do to you.
I won't have a choice.

1321
01:58:04,879 --> 01:58:06,530
Bella, please, come.

1322
01:58:06,630 --> 01:58:08,630
Wait.

1323
01:58:09,800 --> 01:58:12,775
Is he gonna hurt me? Read his mind.

1324
01:58:19,727 --> 01:58:21,727
Jake,

1325
01:58:27,485 --> 01:58:29,485
I love you.

1326
01:58:33,824 --> 01:58:35,824
So, please,

1327
01:58:40,039 --> 01:58:42,123
don't make me choose,

1328
01:58:47,880 --> 01:58:49,880
'cause it'll be him.

1329
01:58:53,177 --> 01:58:55,177
It’s always been him.

1330
01:59:02,520 --> 01:59:04,520
Bella...

1331
01:59:11,654 --> 01:59:15,479
Goodbye, Jacob.
- No, you don't speak for her.

1332
01:59:19,537 --> 01:59:21,538
Bella, get out of here.

1333
01:59:23,332 --> 01:59:25,332
Stop.

1334
01:59:26,877 --> 01:59:28,154
Stop.

1335
01:59:28,254 --> 01:59:31,994
You can't hurt each other
without hurting me.

1336
01:59:50,359 --> 01:59:52,359
Jake.

1337
02:00:06,542 --> 02:00:08,542
He's right.

1338
02:00:09,086 --> 02:00:11,721
You shouldn't become what l am.

1339
02:00:16,427 --> 02:00:18,428
I can't do this alone.

1340
02:00:21,098 --> 02:00:23,138
Then, please, just wait.

1341
02:00:30,065 --> 02:00:32,692
Just give me five years.

1342
02:00:38,282 --> 02:00:40,282
That's too long.

1343
02:00:44,413 --> 02:00:46,413
Then three?

1344
02:00:50,586 --> 02:00:52,586
You're so stubborn.

1345
02:00:54,256 --> 02:00:56,381
What are you waiting for?

1346
02:01:05,100 --> 02:01:08,144
l have one condition...

1347
02:01:10,648 --> 02:01:13,538
...if you want me to do it myself.

1348
02:01:17,238 --> 02:01:19,238
What's the condition?

1349
02:01:19,657 --> 02:01:21,657
And then forever.

1350
02:01:23,160 --> 02:01:25,285
That's what I’m asking.

1351
02:01:36,382 --> 02:01:38,382
Marry me, Bella.
